{"article_id":"bXFibEJZCGjvcQkP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas ripped his colleagues","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"for blocking President Donald Trump ' s request","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to end the DACA program .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"DACA ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"which stands for Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"prevents young people","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"who were brought to the U.S. illegally as children","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"from being deported for a period of time .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"The program was put in place by former President Barack Obama in 2012 .","depth":3},{"id":9,"text":"\" Today ' s decision must be recognized for what it is :","depth":4},{"id":10,"text":"an effort","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"to avoid a politically controversial but legally correct decision , \"","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Thomas wrote in his dissent .","depth":3},{"id":13,"text":"The court ruled 5-4","depth":4},{"id":14,"text":"that the Department of Homeland Security 's decision","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"to cancel DACA","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"did not follow proper procedure .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"Chief Justice John Roberts wrote the opinion ,","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"which states","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"that the department does have the ability","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to cancel the program .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"The opinion said","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"the court took issue with the reasons","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"the Trump administration gave","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"for eliminating the program .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"`` The dispute before the Court is not whether DHS may rescind DACA .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"All parties agree","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that it may .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"The dispute is instead primarily about the procedure","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"the agency followed","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"in doing so , \"","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"he wrote ,","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"adding","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"the department 's decision","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"to terminate the program","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"was `` arbitrary and capricious . ''","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Thomas blasted his colleagues for giving the \" green light for future political battles to be fought in this Court","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"rather than where they rightfully belong","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"- the political branches . \"","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"`` The majority does not even attempt to explain","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"why a court has the authority","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"to scrutinize an agency ' s policy reasons","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"for rescinding an unlawful program under the arbitrary and capricious microscope , ''","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"Thomas said .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"`` The decision","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to countermand an unlawful agency action","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"is clearly reasonable .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"So long as the agency ' s determination of illegality is sound ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"our review should be at an end . ''","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"He said","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"the majority ' s opinion supports the idea","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"that a president is \" not only permitted ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"but required ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"to continue administering unlawful programs","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"that it inherited from a previous administration . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":109,"left":67,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":67,"left":63,"right":66,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":63,"left":62,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":62,"left":57,"right":61,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":57,"left":0,"right":56,"r